cnLesBusTable.name: cnLesBusTable
cnLesBusTable.description: smart les/bus enable and unique server id.

cnLesBusConfIndex.name: cnLesBusConfIndex
cnLesBusConfIndex.description: A value which uniquely identifies a conceptual row in the lesConfTable.

cnLesBusSmartLes.name: cnLesBusSmartLes
cnLesBusSmartLes.description: This object is used to turn on/off smart les/bus.

cnLesBusServerId.name: cnLesBusServerId
cnLesBusServerId.description: This object specifies the unique server id among all les/bus pairs that serve the same elan.

cnLesBusPeerTable.name: cnLesBusPeerTable
cnLesBusPeerTable.description: The LES/BUS peer table. This table contains the all LES/BUS pairs of the ELANs managed by the agent. The LES/BUS instantiated by the agent is also included in this table. Other LES/BUS pairs that are not running in the same system being managed by the agent are configured by the user. Note that there is no verification protocol supported for the entries configured by the user.

cnLesBusPeerEntry.name: cnLesBusPeerEntry
cnLesBusPeerEntry.description: A pair of LES/BUS for the ELAN managed by the agent.

cnLesBusIndex.name: cnLesBusIndex
cnLesBusIndex.description: Index into the ELAN this pair of LES/BUS is servicing.

cnLesBusPeerIndex.name: cnLesBusPeerIndex
cnLesBusPeerIndex.description: An arbitrary integer which uniquly identifies a pair of LES/BUS within an ELAN.

cnLesBusPeerLesAddr.name: cnLesBusPeerLesAddr
cnLesBusPeerLesAddr.description: The ATM address of the LES.

cnLesBusPeerBusAddr.name: cnLesBusPeerBusAddr
cnLesBusPeerBusAddr.description: The ATM address of the BUS.

cnLesBusPeerStatus.name: cnLesBusPeerStatus
cnLesBusPeerStatus.description: This object is used to create or destroy an entry from this table. This object also reflect the current state of the peer LES/BUS. If both peer LES and BUS are connected to this LES/BUS, then active(3) is returned when read, otherwise inactive(4) will be returned.

cnLesBusPortTable.name: cnLesBusPortTable
cnLesBusPortTable.description: The ATM port a LESBUS uses to establish virtual circuits(VCC). A User can choose to either select the any-port capability, which let the LESBUS choose whichever the ATM port is available. Or the user can specify a list of ATM ports the LESBUS will request the VCCs. When a list of ATM ports are specified, There are four objects used for specifying the ATM port numbers. The object cnLesBusPortAtmPort1 is used first, the object cnLesBusPortAtmPort2 second if the first failed and so on.

cnLesBusPortEntry.name: cnLesBusPortEntry
cnLesBusPortEntry.description: Each entry represent a LESBUS maintained by this agent. The entries are indexed by the same index (LesBusIndex) from the LesBusConfigTable defined in the ATM Forum LESBUS MIB.

cnLesBusPortElanIndex.name: cnLesBusPortElanIndex
cnLesBusPortElanIndex.description: An index to the LESBUS pair that will use this table.

cnLesBusPortIndex.name: cnLesBusPortIndex
cnLesBusPortIndex.description: An index to an entry in the port table

cnLesBusCardId.name: cnLesBusCardId
cnLesBusCardId.description: Card ID of the ATM card.

cnLesBusPortId.name: cnLesBusPortId
cnLesBusPortId.description: Port ID of the ATM port.

cnLesBusPortStatus.name: cnLesBusPortStatus
cnLesBusPortStatus.description: The object is used to create or destroy an entry from this table. This object also reflect the current state of the port entry. If the client uses this port to join the ELAN, then active(3) is returned when read.

cnLecServerTable.name: cnLecServerTable
cnLecServerTable.description: The LE Client's user configured server list. The LEC can use any pf the servers defined in this table. The search order matches the order of the entries in the table.

cnLecServerEntry.name: cnLecServerEntry
cnLecServerEntry.description: A LE server that the LEC can use.

cnLecServerIndex.name: cnLecServerIndex
cnLecServerIndex.description: An index to the lec server table.

cnLecServerType.name: cnLecServerType
cnLecServerType.description: The field specifies how the the LEC can get to the server and the server type (LES or LECS). The LEC can connect to either the LECS via ILMI/PVC/ATM address or the LES via ATm address.

cnLecServerAddress.name: cnLecServerAddress
cnLecServerAddress.description: The field specifies the ATM address (20 octets) of the server when an ATM address is needed. If an ATM address is not needed, zero will be returned when read.

cnLecServerStatus.name: cnLecServerStatus
cnLecServerStatus.description: The object is used to create or destroy an entry from this table. The entry is always in active state once created.

cnLecPortTable.name: cnLecPortTable
cnLecPortTable.description: The ATM port a LEC uses to establish virtual circuits(VCC). A User can choose to either select the any-port capability, which let the LEC choose whichever the ATM port is available. Or the user can specify a list of ATM ports the LEC will request the VCCs. When a list of ATM ports are specified, There are four objects used for specifying the ATM port numbers. The object cnLecPortAtmPort1 is used first, the object cnlecPortAtmPort2 second if the first failed and so on.

cnLecPortEntry.name: cnLecPortEntry
cnLecPortEntry.description: Each entry represent a LEC maintained by this agent. The entries are indexed by the same index (lecIndex) from the lecConfigTable defined in the ATM Forum LEC MIB.

cnLecPortlecIndex.name: cnLecPortlecIndex
cnLecPortlecIndex.description: An index to the LEC that will use this table.

cnLecPortIndex.name: cnLecPortIndex
cnLecPortIndex.description: An index to an entry in the port table

cnLecCardId.name: cnLecCardId
cnLecCardId.description: Card ID of the ATM card.

cnLecPortId.name: cnLecPortId
cnLecPortId.description: Port ID of the ATM port.

cnLecPortStatus.name: cnLecPortStatus
cnLecPortStatus.description: The object is used to create or destroy an entry from this table. This object also reflect the current state of the port entry. If the client uses this port to join the ELAN, then active(3) is returned when read.

cnLecsPortTable.name: cnLecsPortTable
cnLecsPortTable.description: The ATM port a Lecs uses to establish virtual circuits(VCC). A User can choose to either select the any-port capability, which let the Lecs choose whichever the ATM port is available. Or the user can specify a list of ATM ports the Lecs will request the VCCs. When a list of ATM ports are specified, There are four objects used for specifying the ATM port numbers. The object cnLecsPortAtmPort1 is used first, the object cnLecsPortAtmPort2 second if the first failed and so on.

cnLecsPortEntry.name: cnLecsPortEntry
cnLecsPortEntry.description: Each entry represent a Lecs maintained by this agent. The entries are indexed by the same index (LecsIndex) from the LecsConfigTable defined in the ATM Forum Lecs MIB.

cnLecsIndex.name: cnLecsIndex
cnLecsIndex.description: An index to the Lecs pair that will use this table.

cnLecsPortIndex.name: cnLecsPortIndex
cnLecsPortIndex.description: An index to an entry in the port table

cnLecsCardId.name: cnLecsCardId
cnLecsCardId.description: Card ID of the ATM card.

cnLecsPortId.name: cnLecsPortId
cnLecsPortId.description: Port ID of the ATM port.

cnLecsPortStatus.name: cnLecsPortStatus
cnLecsPortStatus.description: The object is used to create or destroy an entry from this table. This object also reflect the current state of the port entry. If the client uses this port to join the ELAN, then active(3) is returned when read.

cnLecsExtnEntry.name: cnLecsExtnEntry
cnLecsExtnEntry.description: An extension to the lecsConfEntry which contains objects associated to a LECS.

cnLecsExtnAtmAddressSelect.name: cnLecsExtnAtmAddressSelect
cnLecsExtnAtmAddressSelect.description: LECS ATM Address selection. atmForum(1) - ATM Forum well known ATM Address. userDefined(2) - User defined ATM Address.

atmCallRoutingConfigEntry.name: atmCallRoutingConfigEntry
atmCallRoutingConfigEntry.description: Objects atmCallRoutingId, and atmCallRoutingRowStatus are required during row creation. And object elanLesRowStatus is required during row deletion.

atmCallRoutingCard.name: atmCallRoutingCard
atmCallRoutingCard.description: This field indicates the ATM card id.

atmCallRoutingPort.name: atmCallRoutingPort
atmCallRoutingPort.description: This field indicates ATM port id.

atmCallRoutingCost.name: atmCallRoutingCost
atmCallRoutingCost.description: The cost of the route. range from 0 to 255 with 0 the least cost. This is the link group id if atmCallRoutingType is linkGroup.

atmCallRoutingEnable.name: atmCallRoutingEnable
atmCallRoutingEnable.description: Enable bit of the call routing. 1 = enable routing 2 = disable routing

atmCallRoutingRowStatus.name: atmCallRoutingRowStatus
atmCallRoutingRowStatus.description: The current status of the entry. Entries may be added by specifying a value of valid, and removed by setting the status to invalid.

cnLaneSig.name: cnLaneSig
cnLaneSig.description: Global parameter to enable or disable signalling in the box.

cnLaneEdge.name: cnLaneEdge
cnLaneEdge.description: Global configuration of the box edge: configured as LEC only services edgeAndswitch: configured as full LANE services switchOnly: configured as switch only services.

cnLaneNetPrefix.name: cnLaneNetPrefix
cnLaneNetPrefix.description: Useful if the box is configured as edgeAndswitch.

cnLaneStatusEnquiryEnable.name: cnLaneStatusEnquiryEnable
cnLaneStatusEnquiryEnable.description: This object is used to enable or disable the Status enquiry. Note that this parametwer is used only if the ATM signalling is enabled.

cnLaneStatusEnquiryInterval.name: cnLaneStatusEnquiryInterval
cnLaneStatusEnquiryInterval.description: The Status Enquiry requests for each call are sent periodically at this interval (in secs). Note that this parametwer is used only if the ATM signalling and atmSysStatusEnquiryEnable are enabled.

cnLecConfigExtnTable.description: This the extension table of lecConfigTable.

cnLecConfigExtnEntry.name: cnLecConfigExtnEntry
cnLecConfigExtnEntry.description: Each table entry contains configuration information for one LAN Emulation Client.
